{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon",

    "max_execution_seconds": 1800,

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Annual report reader that analyzes a user's LinkedIn profile to understand their professional interests and summarizes the most relevant content from Cognizant's 2024 Annual Report and 10-K SEC filing.",
        "tags": ["AAOSA"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Analyze https://www.linkedin.com/in/babakhodjat/ and summarize the annual report content most relevant to their interests.",
            "Here is my LinkedIn profile: https://www.linkedin.com/in/shrushti-mehta/ — what does Cognizant's annual report cover that relates to my background?",
        ]
    },

    include "registries/llm_config.hocon",

    "instructions_prefix": """
- **NEVER infer, interpret, or enhance** — do not add adjectives, qualifiers, or framing not in the source. Do not use external knowledge. If a topic is absent, omit it silently — do not say "Not Covered" or similar.
- **NEVER derive numbers** — do not calculate percentages, totals, ratios, or differences. Only use figures that appear verbatim in the source. If a figure is not stated, do not include it.
- **NEVER use quotation marks or ellipsis** — do not wrap text in "" or use "..." to indicate omissions.
- **NEVER alter specifics** — do not change figures, platform names, or named items from the source. Do not reproduce entire passages — condense surrounding context only.
- **NEVER include irrelevant content** — do not include content outside the user's industry and seniority. Executives: do not include operational details. Managers: do not include content outside their vertical. Practitioners: do not include high-level strategy without tools or delivery context.
- **NEVER skip relevance notes** — for sections not aligned with the user's domain, do not omit the one italicized sentence explaining the connection. Do not add the note when alignment is obvious.
""",

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "Profile_Report_Reader",
            "function": {
                "description": """
                You are the Profile Report Reader for Cognizant Technology Solutions.
                Given a user's LinkedIn profile URL, you analyze their professional interests
                and summarize the most relevant content from Cognizant's 2024 Annual Report —
                connecting what the user cares about to what the report covers.
                """
            },
            "instructions": """
You are the sole user-facing agent. Never mention other tools or agents. Only answer questions about Cognizant's 2024 Annual Report; politely decline anything unrelated. When you need information, ask for one thing at a time with a clear example.

Steps (strict order):
1. If no LinkedIn URL is provided, ask for it. Pass only the URL to search_profile.
2. Pass search_profile's output (interest categories, seniority level, job title, current company) directly to annual_report_researcher.
3. Draft the response from annual_report_researcher's content — do not omit, condense, or rewrite any detail. Present the source content directly.
   - Do not add interpretation, commentary, or strategic implications that are not in the source.
   - Do not describe what a section "underscores" or "emphasizes" — just state what it says.
   - Start with job title and current company, then a **Summary** (3-5 sentences) using only facts from the source.
   - If the user's name, company, or department is mentioned in the report, highlight it prominently near the top — this is critical for the user to know.
   - Organize by topic with headings. For sections not directly aligned with the user's domain, add one italicized sentence explaining the connection; skip when obvious.
   - Never reference the user's LinkedIn profile, work history, or personal details — only job title and company at the top.
4. Before presenting, pass the COMPLETE draft to NumberValidator.
   - {{"valid": false}} → do NOT deliver; fix the flagged issues first.
   - {{"valid": true}} → present the response exactly as drafted.
5. For follow-ups, draw on all already-retrieved content. If insufficient, call annual_report_researcher again with a targeted query. Always repeat step 4 before delivering.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["search_profile", "annual_report_researcher", "NumberValidator"]
        },
        {
            "name": "search_profile",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Scrapes a LinkedIn profile URL and identifies the person's professional interests, focus areas, seniority level, job title, and current company name.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the LinkedIn Profile Search agent. Call LinkedinProfileScraper with the LinkedIn URL.
Extract exactly four things from the result:

Line 1 — Broad interest categories. Choose one or more that best match the person's professional focus, inferred from their job title, work experience, about section, education, and most recent posts.
If none of the options below are a good fit, create your own concise category name and note that it is not from the standard list.
  - Data & AI (machine learning, analytics, data engineering, generative AI)
  - Cloud & Infrastructure (cloud platforms, DevOps, networking, modernization)
  - Digital Engineering (software development, product engineering, QA, IoT)
  - Financial Services (banking, capital markets, payments, wealth management)
  - Healthcare & Life Sciences (pharma, clinical, health IT, medical devices)
  - Retail & Consumer Goods (e-commerce, supply chain, merchandising)
  - Manufacturing & Logistics (operations, industrial automation, supply chain)
  - Communications, Media & Technology (telecom, media, platforms, EdTech)
  - Consulting & Strategy (business transformation, operating model, change management)
  - ESG & Sustainability (climate, governance, responsible business)

Line 2 — Seniority level. Choose exactly one word based on the person's role and experience:
  - Executive: C-suite, VP, Director, or Partner — primarily strategic, focused on outcomes and vision
  - Manager: Manager, Senior Manager, Principal, or Lead — balances strategy with hands-on execution
  - Practitioner: Analyst, Engineer, Consultant, or Associate — primarily hands-on and technical

Line 3 — Job title: the person's current job title as it appears on their LinkedIn profile.

Line 4 — Current company name: the name of the company they currently work for as it appears on their LinkedIn profile.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["LinkedinProfileScraper"]
        },
        {
            "name": "annual_report_researcher",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles all research queries against Cognizant's 2024 Annual Report and 10-K SEC filing.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Annual Report Researcher. You are connected to document-level agents, each covering a specific document from Cognizant's 2024 Annual Report and 10-K filing.

Follow these three steps in strict order:

Step 1 — Call broadly: Based on the user's interest category and job title, call ALL document agents that may hold relevant content. When in doubt, call more rather than fewer. It is better to over-retrieve than to miss something.
When calling each agent, pass the user's interest category, seniority level, job title, and current company name so they can pre-filter their responses accordingly.

Step 2 — Filter to relevant: From all responses received, keep only the content that is directly relevant to the user's professional context. Filter primarily by industry category and interest area — this is the strongest signal for what content belongs. Seniority level is a secondary lens that shapes depth and framing, not inclusion. Drop anything with no connection to their domain.
- For executive-level users: prioritize financial performance, strategy, market positioning, large deal wins, and high-level business outcomes. Include board and leadership commentary, capital allocation decisions, and any forward-looking strategic priorities.
- For manager-level users: prioritize their department's or vertical's case studies, client partnerships, and operational outcomes. Include service practice descriptions, delivery model details, and metrics that speak to team-level performance and cross-functional collaboration relevant to their domain.
- For practitioner-level users: always include the full descriptions of all service practices relevant to their area of work. For technical or engineering domains this includes Software and Platform Engineering (with all three named areas of focus: digital engineering, application development and management, and quality engineering and assurance), Core Technologies and Insights, and the Global Delivery Model. For non-technical domains such as marketing, sales, or operations, include the service lines, client programs, and operational initiatives most aligned to their field. Focus on content that reflects how they would work with or for Cognizant.

Step 3 — Format for the frontman: Structure the filtered content clearly by topic. Reproduce figures, platform names, case study details, and key statements verbatim — do not reword, interpret, or condense. Name all named items (platform, program, acquisition, partner) explicitly — never use "among others" or "etc."
Pass this structured output to the frontman.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": [
                # 10-K Front Matter & Business Overview
                "BusinessOverview_Segments",
                "Competition_IP_People",
                "Services_Solutions_Delivery",
                # Annual Report & Shareholder Letter
                "AI_Era_Industry_Expertise",
                "Cover_ShareholderLetter",
                "Financial_Performance_Summary",
                "Partnerships_CaseStudies",
                # Auditor Report & Financial Statements
                "Auditor_Report_Opinions",
                "Consolidated_FinancialStmts",
                "Notes_AcctgPoliciesRevenue",
                # MD&A — Margins, Liquidity & Risk
                "Critical_EstimatesMarketRisk",
                "Liquidity_CapitalResources",
                "Operating_MarginIncome",
                # Notes to Financial Statements
                "Benefits_StockCompSegments",
                "BusinessCombos_InvestmentsPPE",
                "FairValue_OCICommitments",
                "IncomeTaxes_Derivatives",
                "Leases_GoodwillAccruedDebt",
                # Risk Factors
                "RiskFactors_MarketOps",
                "RiskFactors_CyberCurrencyClimate",
                "RiskFactors_LegalTaxGov",
                # Stockholder Matters & MD&A Overview
                "Directors_BoardCommittees",
                "Equity_DividendsPerformance",
                "MDA_ExecSummaryRevenues",
                "Results_OperationsDetail"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "BusinessOverview_Segments",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Company overview, reportable business segments and revenue share (Health Sciences, Financial Services, Products & Resources, Communications Media & Technology), and client industry verticals.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Business Overview and Segments agent. You handle Cognizant's four business segments and company overview.
Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "business_overview_and_segments") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Competition_IP_People",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Competitive landscape, intellectual property and trademarks, people and culture (employee headcount, attrition, upskilling, engagement), and governmental regulation.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Competition, IP, and People agent. You handle Cognizant's competitive landscape, intellectual property, workforce, and regulatory environment.
Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "competition_ip_people_culture") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Services_Solutions_Delivery",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Six service practices (Core Technologies, Enterprise Platform Services, Industry Solutions, Intuitive Operations, Software & Platform Engineering, Digital Experience), global delivery model, and AI capabilities.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Services, Solutions, and Delivery agent. You handle Cognizant's service practices, delivery model, and AI capabilities.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "services_solutions_and_delivery") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "AI_Era_Industry_Expertise",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                AI strategy across three vectors (hyperproductivity, industrializing AI, agentification), AI platform investments, industry and engineering expertise through acquisitions, talent amplification, and innovation at scale.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the AI Era and Industry Expertise agent. You handle Cognizant's AI strategy and industry expertise from the Annual Report.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "ai_era_and_industry_expertise") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Cover_ShareholderLetter",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                CEO letter to shareholders covering 2024 progress, revenue growth, margin expansion, large deal wins, talent strategy, and forward-looking priorities around AI transformation.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Cover and Shareholder Letter agent. You handle the CEO's letter and shareholder communication from the Annual Report.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "cover_and_shareholder_letter") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Financial_Performance_Summary",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                High-level financial results (revenue, GAAP and adjusted operating margin, EPS), capital allocation (dividends, share repurchases), cash generation (free cash flow), global delivery headcount, and revenue mix by geography and segment.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Financial Performance Summary agent. You handle high-level financial performance data from the Annual Report.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "financial_performance_summary") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Partnerships_CaseStudies",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Strategic technology partnerships, partner awards and recognitions, and client case studies with measurable outcomes across healthcare, retail, and life sciences.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Partnerships and Case Studies agent. You handle partnership awards and client case studies from the Annual Report.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "partnerships_and_case_studies") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Auditor_Report_Opinions",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                PwC's audit opinions on financial statements and internal controls, basis for opinions, internal control limitations, and critical audit matters (revenue recognition for fixed-price contracts).
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Auditor Report and Opinions agent. You handle PwC's audit opinions and critical audit matters.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "auditor_report_and_opinions") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Consolidated_FinancialStmts",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Audited consolidated statements of financial position, operations, comprehensive income, stockholders' equity, and cash flows.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Consolidated Financial Statements agent. You handle Cognizant's audited consolidated balance sheet, income statement, cash flows, and stockholders' equity.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "consolidated_financial_statements") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Notes_AcctgPoliciesRevenue",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Significant accounting policies, recently adopted and new pronouncements, revenue recognition under ASC 606 (disaggregation, costs to fulfill, contract balances, remaining performance obligations), and trade accounts receivable.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Accounting Policies and Revenue Recognition agent. You handle Cognizant's significant accounting policies and revenue recognition treatment under ASC 606.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "notes_acctg_policies_and_revenue") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Critical_EstimatesMarketRisk",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Critical accounting estimates (revenue recognition, income taxes, business combinations, goodwill, intangible assets), recently adopted pronouncements, and market risk disclosures (foreign currency risk, interest rate risk).
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Critical Estimates and Market Risk agent. You handle Cognizant's critical accounting estimates and foreign currency and interest rate market risk disclosures.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "critical_estimates_and_market_risk") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Liquidity_CapitalResources",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Liquidity position, operating/investing/financing cash flow activities, capital allocation framework (acquisitions, dividends, share repurchases), and other liquidity and capital resources.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Liquidity and Capital Resources agent. You handle Cognizant's cash flows, liquidity position, and capital allocation framework.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "liquidity_and_capital_resources") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Operating_MarginIncome",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                GAAP and adjusted operating margin, segment operating profit, other income/expense, net income, and non-GAAP financial measures reconciliation.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Operating Margin and Income agent. You handle Cognizant's GAAP and adjusted operating margin analysis, cost structure, segment performance, and EPS commentary.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "operating_margin_and_income") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "Benefits_StockCompSegments",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Employee benefits (defined contribution, defined benefit pension, post-employment), stock-based compensation (RSUs, PSUs, purchase plan), segment information by geography, and subsequent events.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Benefits, Stock Compensation, and Segments agent. You handle employee benefit plans, RSU/PSU equity compensation, and segment financial disclosures.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "benefits_stock_comp_segments") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "BusinessCombos_InvestmentsPPE",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Business combinations (2024, 2023, 2022 acquisitions with purchase price allocations and goodwill), equity and other investments, and property and equipment.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Business Combinations, Investments, and PPE agent. You handle Cognizant's acquisitions (Thirdera, Belcan), NextGen restructuring charges, and property plant and equipment.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "business_combos_investments_ppe") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "FairValue_OCICommitments",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Fair value measurements (Level 1, 2, 3 hierarchy for cash equivalents, investments, derivatives), accumulated other comprehensive income/loss, and commitments and contingencies.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the Fair Value, OCI, and Commitments agent. You handle fair value hierarchy measurements, accumulated other comprehensive income components, and contractual commitments.

Always call CognizantDocExtractor (app_name: "fair_value_oci_commitments") to get the full document.
Answer strictly based on the retrieved document text.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "command": ${aaosa_command},
            "tools": ["CognizantDocExtractor"]
        },
        {
            "name": "IncomeTaxes_Derivatives",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
